Reference-contexts: Spatial data mining, or knowledge discovery in spatial database, refers to the extraction of implicit knowledge, spatial relations, or other patterns not explicitly stored in spatial databases [34]. Previous works in machine learning [17, 38, 39], database systems [50, 51], and statistics <ref> [9, 19, 31, 47] </ref> laid the foundation for research into knowledge discovery in databases. Also, advances in spatial databases, such as spatial data structures [22, 23, 46], spatial reasoning [10, 12], computational geometry [43], etc., paved the way for the study of spatial data mining.
